âœ¨ Project Overview: Email Spam Classification
The Email Spam Classification project is a smart solution designed to automatically identify and filter spam emails using machine learning and natural language processing (NLP). In todayâ€™s digital world, where email communication is essential, spam emails pose risks such as phishing attacks, scams, and productivity loss. This project provides a powerful, automated way to protect users and systems by analyzing the text content of emails and classifying them as spam or ham (not spam).

âš™ï¸ How It Works
The system follows a complete end-to-end machine learning pipeline:

Data Preprocessing: Cleans and transforms raw email text by removing punctuation, stop words, and applying tokenization and vectorization (TF-IDF).

Feature Extraction: Converts textual data into numerical format that a machine learning model can understand.

Model Training: Trains classifiers such as Naive Bayes, Logistic Regression, or Support Vector Machines on labeled data to learn spam patterns.

Prediction & Evaluation: Tests the model on unseen emails and evaluates it using accuracy, precision, recall, F1-score, and a confusion matrix.

